## Evaluation Modes

### Fast Mode (default)
- Single Claude call, `temperature=0.3` for consistency
- Claude self-reports confidence per dimension (0.0–1.0)
- Used when `abs(weighted_score - quality_threshold) > CONFIDENCE_BAND`

### High Confidence Mode
- Three Claude calls at `temperature=0.2`
- Confidence = `1 - normalized_variance_across_runs`
- Triggered when `abs(weighted_score - quality_threshold) <= CONFIDENCE_BAND` (default: 0.75)

```python
CONFIDENCE_BAND = 0.75
HIGH_CONFIDENCE_RUNS = 3
HIGH_CONFIDENCE_TEMPERATURE = 0.2
```

